## Code Map
- Path: (example: wp-content/themes/your-theme/functions.php)
	Purpose: (what this file handles)
	Key symbols: (functions/classes/hooks)
	Notes: (important dependencies or edit cautions)

- Path: style.css
	Purpose: WordPress theme declaration and metadata.
	Key symbols: Theme header comment.
	Notes: Required for WordPress theme detection.

- Path: functions.php
	Purpose: Theme setup and assets enqueue.
	Key symbols: website_flexi_theme_setup, website_flexi_enqueue_assets.
	Notes: Registers menu and loads CSS/JS.

- Path: header.php
	Purpose: Shared page header and navigation.
	Key symbols: wp_head, wp_nav_menu, wp_body_open.
	Notes: Primary menu location is "primary".

- Path: footer.php
	Purpose: Shared footer with copyright and wp_footer.
	Key symbols: wp_footer.
	Notes: Common footer text can be edited here.

- Path: front-page.php
	Purpose: Custom homepage layout and service sections.
	Key symbols: $pillars, $offers, $services arrays, section IDs offers/services/contact.
	Notes: Main business copy, signal strip ticker, and animation hooks are here.

- Path: index.php
	Purpose: Fallback template for posts/pages if no specific template exists.
	Key symbols: have_posts, the_post, the_content.
	Notes: Keep as minimal safe fallback.

- Path: assets/css/main.css
	Purpose: Main visual system and responsive styling.
	Key symbols: CSS variables, .hero-glow, .signal-strip, .glass-card, .reveal-stagger.
	Notes: Controls futuristic style, gradients, motion, and responsive layout.

- Path: assets/js/main.js
	Purpose: Scroll reveal animation behavior.
	Key symbols: IntersectionObserver, stagger delays, counter animation, parallax.
	Notes: Handles reveal timing, animated counters, and parallax movement.

